                <h4>What is the voting age population of Bolivar, West Virginia?</h4>
                <p>
                    The total voting age population of Bolivar, West Virginia, meaning US citizens 18 or older, is 945.  The voting age population is 52.6% male and 47.4% female.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Bolivar, West Virginia residents are senior citizens?</h4>
                    <p>
                        According to the latest census statistics, 14.7% of
                        the residents of Bolivar are 65 or older.
                    </p>
                

                
                    

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    
                    
                    <h4>What are the racial demographics of Bolivar, West Virginia?</h4>
                    <p>The racial demographics of Bolivar are 89.8% White, 3.9% Two or more races, 3.4% Black, 1.9% Other and 1.1% Asian. Additionally, 2.8% of the population identifies as Hispanic.</p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Bolivar, West Virginia residents are below the poverty line?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Bolivar, 9.6% of
                    residents have an income below the poverty line, and the child poverty rate
                    is 16.2%.
                    On a per-household basis,
                    3.7% of families are below
                    the poverty line in Bolivar.
                    </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Bolivar, West Virginia residents are in the labor force?</h4>
                    <p>
                    Among those aged 16 and older, 71.7% of
                    Bolivar residents are in the labor force.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                <h4>What are the education levels among Bolivar, West Virginia residents?</h4>
                <p>Among the adult population 25 years old and over,
                    94.6% of
                    Bolivar residents have at least a high school degree or
                    equivalent, 31.2%
                    have a bachelor's degree and 10.7%
                    have a graduate or professional degree.
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of Bolivar, West Virginia residents speak a non-English language at home?</h4>
                <p>
                Among Bolivar residents aged 5 and older, 3.5% of them speak a non-English language at home.
                Broken down by language:
                0.6% of residents speak Spanish at home,
                1.0% speak an Indo-European language, and
                1.2% speak an Asian language.

                </p>
                

                
    


                
                
                    <h4>What is the unemployment rate in Bolivar, West Virginia?</h4>
                    <p>
                        The unemployment rate in Bolivar is 5.7%, which is calculated among residents aged 16 or older who are in the labor force.
                    </p>

                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Bolivar, West Virginia residents work for the government?</h4>
                    <p>
